abstract: Another hearing, a major report on the Russia investigation, and how the two converged.
snippet: Another hearing, a major report on the Russia investigation, and how the two converged.
lead_paragraph: Monday was a big news day in Washington. In addition to the hearing, the Justice Department’s inspector general released a much-anticipated report on the  investigation into links between Russia and the Trump campaign, which found the F.B.I. had sufficient reason to open the inquiry.

abstract: By the time the Justice Department inspector general’s report was released, the president and his supporters had moved on in their effort to convince Americans of the enemies arrayed against him.
snippet: By the time the Justice Department inspector general’s report was released, the president and his supporters had moved on in their effort to convince Americans of the enemies arrayed against him.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump and his allies spent months promising that a report on the origins of the F.B.I.’s Russia investigation would be a kind of Rosetta Stone for Trump-era conspiracy enthusiasts — the key to unlocking the secrets of a government plot to keep Mr. Trump from being elected in 2016.

abstract: U.S. House of Representatives Judiciary Committee Chairman Jerrold Nadler closed his panel's impeachment hearing on Monday with a condemnation of President Donald Trump's conduct as a continuing threat to the country's elections and democratic system of government.
snippet: U.S. House of Representatives Judiciary Committee Chairman Jerrold Nadler closed his panel's impeachment hearing on Monday with a condemnation of President Donald Trump's conduct as a continuing threat to the country's elections and democratic sys...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. House of Representatives Judiciary Committee Chairman Jerrold Nadler closed his panel's impeachment hearing on Monday with a condemnation of President Donald Trump's conduct as a continuing threat to the country's elections and democratic system of government.
headline_main: U.S. House Judiciary Chief Nadler: Trump Conduct 'Clearly Impeachable'
headline_print_headline: U.S. House Judiciary Chief Nadler: Trump Conduct 'Clearly Impeachable'

abstract: Protests and parliamentary bickering reigned as the House Judiciary Committee formally heard arguments for and against President Trump’s impeachment.
snippet: Protests and parliamentary bickering reigned as the House Judiciary Committee formally heard arguments for and against President Trump’s impeachment.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Two minutes into Monday’s historic House Judiciary Committee hearing into the impeachment of President Trump — even before Representative Jerrold Nadler, the chairman, issued the customary call for decorum — a protester, screaming that Mr. Nadler was committing treason, was dragged out of the grand columned hearing room by the Capitol Police.

abstract: Senior U.S. and Canadian officials were set to fly to Mexico City on Tuesday to work on the final changes to a languishing North American trade pact that could clear the way for a vote in the U.S. Congress before the end of the year.
snippet: Senior U.S. and Canadian officials were set to fly to Mexico City on Tuesday to work on the final changes to a languishing North American trade pact that could clear the way for a vote in the U.S. Congress before the end of the year.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senior U.S. and Canadian officials were set to fly to Mexico City on Tuesday to work on the final changes to a languishing North American trade pact that could clear the way for a vote in the U.S. Congress before the end of the year.
headline_main: U.S., Canadian Officials Converge on Mexico City to Seal Final Changes to Trade Deal
headline_print_headline: U.S., Canadian Officials Converge on Mexico City to Seal Final Changes to Trade Deal

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump does not want to implement the next round of scheduled tariffs against Chinese goods on Dec. 15, but he wants "movement" from China to avoid them, U.S. Agriculture Secretary Sonny Perdue said on Monday.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump does not want to implement the next round of scheduled tariffs against Chinese goods on Dec. 15, but he wants "movement" from China to avoid them, U.S. Agriculture Secretary Sonny Perdue said on Monday.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - U.S. President Donald Trump does not want to implement the next round of scheduled tariffs against Chinese goods on Dec. 15, but he wants "movement" from China to avoid them, U.S. Agriculture Secretary Sonny Perdue said on Monday.
headline_main: Trump Wants 'Movement' From China to Avoid Dec. 15 Tariffs-U.S. Agriculture Secretary
headline_print_headline: Trump Wants 'Movement' From China to Avoid Dec. 15 Tariffs-U.S. Agriculture Secretary

abstract: General Motors Co confirmed on Monday it agreed to loan $40 million to an electric vehicle start-up to facilitate the acquisition of its shuttered Lordstown Assembly plant in Ohio.
snippet: General Motors Co confirmed on Monday it agreed to loan $40 million to an electric vehicle start-up to facilitate the acquisition of its shuttered Lordstown Assembly plant in Ohio.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — General Motors Co confirmed on Monday it agreed to loan $40 million to an electric vehicle start-up to facilitate the acquisition of its shuttered Lordstown Assembly plant in Ohio.
headline_main: GM Loans $40 Million to Firm to Acquire, Retool Shuttered Lordstown, Ohio, Factory
headline_print_headline: GM Loans $40 Million to Firm to Acquire, Retool Shuttered Lordstown, Ohio, Factory

abstract: The inspector general provided a close look at what seemed at times to be a bungled relationship between Christopher Steele and the bureau.
snippet: The inspector general provided a close look at what seemed at times to be a bungled relationship between Christopher Steele and the bureau.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The F.B.I. team landed in Rome in early October 2016 for a crucial meeting: to question Christopher Steele, a former British intelligence officer, about evidence he had gathered suggesting that Donald J. Trump’s presidential campaign might be conspiring with Russia.

abstract: A new subpoena from the state attorney general seeks, among other things, records related to campaign finance and to the gun group’s charitable arm.
snippet: A new subpoena from the state attorney general seeks, among other things, records related to campaign finance and to the gun group’s charitable arm.
lead_paragraph: The New York State attorney general has issued a new subpoena to the National Rifle Association, deepening her eight-month investigation and providing fresh clues about where it is headed, according to people with knowledge of the document.
